The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning to enable an artificial agent to acquire physical intuition through interaction with the environment. This involves learning policies that are parametrized by a goal, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of physics simulation and block stacking tasks also suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the goal-oriented nature of the learning framework may also relate to control systems (cs.SY).
